PCF Workbench gallery-visibility marker.

This file hides MAILoopBroken from the default sample gallery shown by
`try-pcf-workbench.bat`. The control is still fully usable from the
command line via `pcf-harness start --path samples\MAILoopBroken\MAILoopBroken`
— the marker just keeps it out of the first-impression gallery.

MAILoopBroken is the AI-build-loop demo control with deliberately bad
patterns (banned APIs, perf antipatterns, a11y issues) so the loop has
something to detect. Showing it to a new user without context would be
confusing.
